BREAST-COMPOSITION: fibro fatty and glandular breast parenchyma (ACR B)
FINDINGS: A well-defined irregular soft opacity with spiculated margins and foci of microcalcifications seen in the lower quadrant of the breast causing mild nipple retraction suggests a malignant lesion (BIRADS 5). The skin and pectoral muscle appear normal. No significant axillary adenopathy is observed.
